A redox-regulated disulphide may form between Glutamate receptor ionotropic, NMDA 1 and Glutamate receptor ionotropic, NMDA 2A at these cysteines. However, the redox score of this cysteine pair is lower than any known redox-active disulphide.

4nf6 B 32 B 39
